## How to install

It is advised to install autoreconf as it is used when installing one of the Node packages. For Ubuntu/Debian run:

    sudo apt-get install autoconf

Install Node packages:

    npm install


## How to run

1. Copy .env.example to .env and edit PORT and ASKSCRIPT_SERVER_URL.

2. Run:

    npm run build

3. Run: 

    npm start


## Changing PORT:
You can change port either by editing PORT in .env file or by setting an environment variable PORT, e.g.:

    PORT=1234 npm start


## Additional notes

Some files come or are inspired by https://github.com/microsoft/TypeScript-Node-Starter (MIT) and https://github.com/Coffeekraken/code-playground (MIT).

